*Lagala* je da će doći, ali nije stigla. (She lied that she would come, but she didn't arrive.)

Ona nije *lagala*, već je preuveličala. (She didn't lie, but she exaggerated.)

Njegove reči su bile pune laži, čim sam to uvidela, znala sam da je *lagao*. (His words were full of lies, as soon as I realized that, I knew he was lying.)

Ona se osećala loše što je *lagala*, pa je ispričala istinu. (She felt bad for lying, so she told the truth.)

Ona je rekla da je bila tamo, ali je u stvari *lagala*. (She said she had been there, but she was actually lying.)